<BR>
ISBN 92-0-155386-2
<BR>
Price: 620 Austrian Schillings
<P>
<B>
Energy and Nuclear Power Planning in Developing Countries
<BR>
<I>Technical Reports Series No. 245</I>
</B>
<P>
The major objective of this publication is to familiarize energy
specialists in developing countries with the fundamental elements
of comprehensive national energy planning. The book goes into the
many technical and economic aspects which are involved in energy
planning in general and which also have to be taken into account
when considering the utilization of nuclear power in a national
energy network. It is further intended for use as a training
manual
or textbook.
<P>
<I>Contents:</I> Introduction: Energy and development; Chapter 1.
The energy system: Technical, economic and planning issues; Part
I:
Energy demand and rational energy supply; Chapter 2. Energy
demand
and demand management; Chapter 3. Primary energy resources:
Inventory, reserves and production potential; Chapter 4.
Development of some newer and renewable primary energy resources;
Chapter 5. Intermediate energy forms; Chapter 6. Electrical
energy;
Chapter 7. Energy transport, distribution and storage; Chapter 8.
Improved energy husbandry - energy conservation; Chapter 9.
Environmental effects and other constraints to energy
development;
Part II: Economic aspects of energy development; Chapter 10.
Basic
concepts of energy economics; Chapter 11. Electricity generation
cost of nuclear and fossil-fuelled power plants; Chapter 12.
Financial aspects; Part III: World energy development; Chapter
14.
Energy in industrialized countries; Chapter 15. Energy in
developing countries; Part IV: Energy planning; Chapter 16.
Optimization of energy supply and utilization - the increasing
role
of electricity; Chapter 17. Energy planning; Chapter 18.
Launching
conditions and implementation of a nuclear power programme.
