S ISBN 92-0-323082-3
<BR>
Price: 140 Austrian Schillings
<P>
<B>
Operational Safety of Nuclear Power Plants
<BR>
<I>Proceedings Series</I>
</B>
<P>
Proceedings of a symposium, Marseilles, France, 2-6 May 1983. The
subjects dealt with varied from activities for safe operation to
emergency preparedness. Commercial nuclear power has a very good
safety record, maintained by its long tradition of attention to
safety, and it compares very favourably with other industries in
this regard. However, designers and operating organizations are
still devoting considerable efforts to achieving even higher
levels
of safety.
<P>
<I>Contents:</I> (Vol.1) Activities for safe operation;
Management
and training of personnel; Human factors and the man-machine
interface; (Vol. 2) Design improvement for safe operation;
Feedback
of operating experience; International activities to improve
safety; Emergency preparedness.
