STI/DOC/10/312 (234 pp., 97 figures; 1990)
<BR>
ISBN 92-0-155090-1
<BR>
Price: 700 Austrian Schillings
<P>
<B>
Nuclear Heat Application
<BR>
<I>Proceedings Series</I>
</B>
<P>
Proceedings of a meeting, Cracow, Poland, 5-9 December 1983. The
purpose of the meeting was to provide an opportunity to review
and
assess the status and the progress made in reactors and systems
for
nuclear heat application, to explore broadly the technical and
economic potential along with environmental and safety aspects,
and
to identify areas where additional research and development would
be needed.
<P>
<I>Contents:</I> Summary report on the Technical Committee
Meeting;
Prospects for nuclear heat applications; Nuclear power plants as
a
heat source - experience, reactor concepts, current projects and
future plans: Part 1. Low-temperature nuclear heat sources. Part
2.
High-temperature nuclear heat sources; Technical aspects of
nuclear
heat applications: Part 1. Low-temperature heat applications;
Part
2. High-temperature heat applications; Safety requirements and
regulatory aspects; Economics.
<P>
STI/PUB/679 (420 pp., 143 figures; 1984)
<BR>
ISBN 92-0-051084-1
<BR>
Price: 980 Austrian Schillings
<P>
<B>
Nuclear Power Plant Control and Instrumentation 1982
<BR>
<I>Proceedings Series</I>
</B>
<P>
Proceedings of a symposium, Munich, Germany, 11-15 October 1982.
The symposium covered: the advantages of the increased use of
computers for supervising and controlling plant operation; the
development of advanced computerized systems for operator
support;
the introduction of computers and microprocessors in plant
protection systems; the introduction of computerized systems for
control of reactor power, reactor water level and reactor
pressure
as well as for reactor startup and shutdown; the design of
control
systems aiming at improvements in man-machine communication; and
the use of simulators for operator training and for the further
design and development of control systems.
<P>
<I>Contents:</I> Experience with control and instrumentation of
nuclear power plants; Advanced systems for operator support;
Protection systems; Control systems; Measurement techniques;
Reliability, qualification and maintainability.
<P>
STI/PUB/628 (726 pp., 235 figures; 1983)
<BR>
ISBN 92-0-050683-6
<BR>
Price: 1690 Austrian Schillings
<P>
<B>
Nuclear Power Plant Instrumentation and Control: A Guidebook
<BR>
<I>Technical Reports Series No. 239</I>
</B>
<P>
This book gives an account of instrumentation and control
problems
that may present difficulties during any of the many crucial
stages
of planning, procurement, commissioning and operation of a
nuclear
power plant. The present version of the guidebook is mainly
restricted to light water reactors but information on the CANDU
system has been included.
<P>
<I>Contents:</I> Part I: Instrumentation and control of a
country's
first nuclear power plant: Introduction; Organization and
methods;
Technology transfer and national participation; Manpower
development; Nuclear power plant training simulator project;
Various phases of project implementation; Special topics;
Bibliography. Part II. Outline of current water reactor
instrumentation and control for current water reactor fuel
nuclear
power plants; Operator/plant communication; Instrumentation; Main
control systems; Safety systems and safety-related system.
Annexes
I-VI: Instrumentation and control concepts from Canada, France,
the
Federal Republic of Germany, Japan and Sweden.
<P>
STI/DOC/10/239 (386 pp., 135 figures; 1984)
<BR>
ISBN 92-0-155284-X
<BR>
Price: 960 Austrian Schillings
<P>
<B>
Off-gas and Air Cleaning Systems for Accident Conditions in
Nuclear
Power Plants
<BR>
<I>Technical Reports Series No. 358</I>
</B>
<P>
Air cleaning systems are subjected to major challenges under
accident conditions and the potential large source terms require
the highest environmental protection from atmospheric release.
The
objective of this report is to consider the principles involved
and
to survey existing systems and equipment for the mitigation of
the
consequences of abnormal plant operations, including severe
accidents beyond the design basis. Some experiences under
abnormal
conditions and international trends in the development of
accident
air cleaning are also included.
<P>
<I>Contents:</I> 1. Introduction; 2. Source terms; 3. Design
principles; 4. Control of airborne contamination in design basis
accidents; 5. Control of airborne contamination in severe
accidents; 6. Experience and trends; 7. Conclusions and
recommendations; Appendix: Testing of off-gas cleaning equipment
for nuclear power
plants.
<P>
STI/DOC/10/358 (117 pp., 48 figures; 1993)
<BR>
ISBN 92-0-102993-4
<BR>
Price: 400 Austrian Schillings
<P>
<B>
Reactor Coolant and Associated Systems in Nuclear Power Plants: A
Safety Guide
<BR>
<I>Safety Series No. 50-SG-D13</I>
</B>
<P>
This guide covers the safety design considerations for various
reactor coolant and associated systems for operational states and
accident conditions including the selection, sizing and
reliability
aspects. This includes safety systems such as emergency core
cooling,residual heat removal or emergency feed-water systems.
The
detailed design of particular components, e.g. heat exchangers,
pumps and vessels, is not covered. 
<P> 
<I>Contents:</I> Introduction; Extent of the reactor coolant and
associated systems; General design principles; Detailed design
principles; Quality assurance; Annex I: Reactor coolant and
associated systems diagrams; Annex II: Main reactor coolant
system
components; Annex III: Listing of pressure boundary codes and
standards used in some Member States.
<P>
STI/PUB/731 (70 pp., 6 figures; 1986)
<BR>
E ISBN 92-0-123886-X
<BR>
F ISBN 92-0-223887-1
<BR>
R ISBN 92-0-423789-9
<BR>
S ISBN 92-0-323587-6
<BR>
Price: 260 Austrian Schillings
<P>
<B>
Reliability of Reactor Pressure Components
<BR>
<I>Proceedings Series</I>
</B>
<P>
Proceedings of a symposium, Stuttgart, Germany, 21-25 March 1983.
The symposium dealt mainly with reliability concepts and problems
specific to nuclear power reactor pressure components by using
the
following approaches: operating experience; analyses of failure
data; reliability criteria for design, materials selection and
fabrication; operation and inspection of components.
<P>
<I>Contents:</I> Primary circuit; Steam generators; Fabrication
and
materials; Fracture mechanics application; Flaw detection and
sizing; Pumps and valves and pipe cracking; In-service data
acquisition, storage and retrieval with special emphasis on the
use
in data banks for component reliability.
<P>
STI/PUB/645 (415 pp., 226 figures; 1983)
<BR>
ISBN 92-0-050883-9
<BR>
Price: 980 Austrian Schillings
<P>
<B>
Safety Related Instrumentation and Control Systems for Nuclear
Power Plants:  A Safety Guide 
<BR>
<I>Safety Series No. 50-SG-D8</I>
</B>
<P>
This guide deals primarily with design requirements for
instrumentation and control systems that are important to safety,
but are not part of the protection system (Safety Series No.
50-SG-D3). It gives recommendations on instrumentation and
control
systems for the prevention or termination of plant transients to
avoid, if possible, the actuation of safety systems.
<P>
<I>Contents:</I> Introduction; Extent of the I&C systems; Design
basis; Design requirements; Documentation; Appendix: Single
failure
criterion for safety related I&C systems.
<P>
STI/PUB/678 (48 pp., 1 figure; 1984)
<BR>
E ISBN 92-0-623184-7
<BR>
F ISBN 92-0-223085-4
<BR>
R ISBN 92-0-423485-7
<BR>
S ISBN 92-0-323585-X
<BR>
Price: 190 Austrian Schillings
<P>
<B>
Status of and Prospects for Gas Cooled Reactors
<BR>
<I>Technical Reports Series No. 235</I>
</B>
<P>
This report is mainly based on submissions from Member States and
provides technical information on fast and thermal reactors
cooled
by CO<SUB>2</SUB>, helium or N<SUB>2</SUB>O<SUB>4</SUB>.
<P>
<I>Contents:</I> Introduction; Historical development of gas
cooled
reactors up to the present;Technical status of the application of
GCRs; Special features of gas cooled reactors; Annex.
<P>
STI/DOC/10/235 (264 pp., 86 figures; 1984)
<BR>
ISBN 92-0-155084-7
<BR>
Price: 690 Austrian Schillings
<P>
<B>
Status of Liquid Metal Cooled Fast Breeder Reactors
<BR>
<I>Technical Reports Series No. 246</I>
</B>
<P> 
This volume represents a compilation of information on the
technical and developmental status of liquid metal cooled fast
breeder reactors (LMFBRs). The report describes worldwide
activities, including the role of international co-operation, in
this advanced nuclear power technology area. Extensive references
and a bibliography on each of the major topic areas are also
included.
<P>
<I>Contents:</I> Background and overview; National programmes;
LMFBR experience; Reactor physics and core design; Fuels and
materials; Reactor engineering; LMFBR safety; The fuel cycle of
fast breeder reactors; LMFBR deployment; Summary and future
trends.
<P>
STI/DOC/10/246 (677 pp., 157 figures; 1985)
<BR>
ISBN 92-0-155185-1
<BR>
Price: 1650 Austrian Schillings
<P>
<B>
Water Chemistry and Corrosion Problems of Nuclear Power Plants
<BR>
<I>Proceedings Series</I>
</B>
<P>
Proceedings of a symposium, Vienna, 22-26 November 1982. The
symposium contributed to the resolution of such questions as
material selection for reactor systems and components, and
improvement of their corrosion resistance. Another important
topic
was the correct choice of methods for ensuring coolant quality as
required by existing codes and standards and by the need for
reliable plant operation.
<P>
<I>Contents:</I> Experience in water chemistry with boiling,
pressurized and heavy water reactors; Theoretical basis and
modelling of reactor water regimes and corrosion of reactor
structural materials; Technology of coolant purification of
reactor
primary and secondary components; Water chemistry for secondary
circuits of plants with pressurized water reactors; Corrosion and
erosion of structural materials in different types of reactor
environment; Decontamination for nuclear reactor systems.
<P>
STI/PUB/630 (521 pp., 190 figures; 1983)
<BR>
ISBN 92-0-050783-2
<BR>
Price: 1200 Austrian Schillings
