<B><I>
Nuclear Safety Standards (NUSS) publications</I>
<P>
Code on the Safety of Nuclear Power Plants:  Quality Assurance
<BR>
<I>Safety Series No. 50-C-QA (Rev. 1)</I>
</B>
<P>
Principles and objectives for establishment and implementation of
quality assurance programmes applied to both the overall and each
of the constituent activities associated with a nuclear power
plant
or nuclear facility. Encompasses the activities necessary: (a) to
achieve the appropriate quality of the respective item or
service;
and (b) to verify that the required quality is achieved and
objective evidence is produced.
<P>
<I>Contents:</I> Definitions; 1. Introduction; 2. Quality
assurance
programmes; 3. Organization; 4. Document control; 5. Design
control; 6. Procurement control; 7. Control of items; 8. Process
control; 9. Inspection and test control; 10. Non-conformance
control; 11. Corrective actions; 12. Records; 13. Audits.
