of large volumes of waste; 9. Disposal of facility operation,
closure and surveillance; 10. Review of operational experience;
11. Radiation protection and safety plan; 12. Conclusions;
Appendix A. Radiological criteria required to implement the
cleanup of large areas after an accident at a nuclear facility;
Appendix B. A generic method for estimating costs of waste
loading, transportation and disposal; Appendix C. Experience in
Canada with the transportation and long term management of
radioactively contaminated soils; Appendix D. Experience in the
USA with the transportation and disposal of radium contaminated
waste; Appendix E. Transportation and disposal of large volumes
of contaminated material arising from cleanup after the Chernobyl
accident.
