<A NAME=203><B>
Handling of Tritium Bearing Wastes   
<BR>
<I>Technical Reports Series
No. 203</I>
</B></A>
<P>
The generation of nuclear power and reprocessing of nuclear fuel
results in the production of tritium and the possible need to
control the release of tritium contaminated effluents. In
assessing the need for controls, it is necessary to know the
production rates of tritium at different facilities, the
technologies available for separating tritium from different
gaseous and liquid streams, and the methods that can be used for
storage and disposal of tritiated wastes. These topics are
discussed in the present report.
<P>
<I>Contents:</I> 1. Introduction; 2. Tritium sources, production
and release rates; 3. Tritium containment and collection; 4.
