<B>
International Tokamak Reactor: Zero Phase
<BR>
<I>Panel Proceedings Series</I>
</B>
<P>
Report of a workshop, held in Vienna in 4 Sessions in 1979. An
assessment of the scientific and technological basis for the most
ambitious next step in the tokamak approach to the development of
a controlled nuclear fusion reactor. The IAEA convened the INTOR
(International Tokamak Reactor) workshop to assess the existing
database and the required research and development for
construction of the most advanced tokamak in the early 1990s as
an international
project. Representatives from Euratom, Japan, USSR and USA took
part in this study, supported by 100 specialists from these four
participating groups.
