<BODY BGCOLOR=#ffffff>
<CENTER>
<H2>
International Nuclear Information System
</H2>
</CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER>
<A HREF=/worldatom/publications/96pubs/96inis.html><IMG BORDER=0
SRC=/worldatom/publications/grafix/new.gif align=center></A>
</center>
<p>
<CENTER>
<I>
To view the latest <B>1996 publications</B> for this section, click the
above icon.</I>
</CENTER>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<B>
INIS ATOMINDEX
</B>
<P>
A computer produced bibliography issued twice a month in print
and on COM microfiche. This publication contains the full file of
INIS references published since the system's beginning.
<P>
Each issue of <B>INIS Atomindex</B> contains bibliographic
descriptions,
descriptors and, usually, abstracts for all items recorded in the
system, namely books, research reports, patents, journal
articles, conference papers, etc. About 90 000 references per
year are grouped by subject categories. Each issue includes a
personal author index, a corporate entry index, a report,
standard and patent number index, a subject index, and two
conference indexes by date and place. The references are in
English with the titles also given in the original language --
transliterated where necessary. The abstracts are printed in
English and may, in addition, appear in French, Russian or
Spanish, the other official languages of the IAEA. Twenty-four
issues are published per year, cumulative indexes are published
semiannually and annually. The first issue of each year includes
a list of the Journals regularly scanned for in-scope articles.
<P>
STI/PUB/245 (approx. 24 000 pp., 21 x 30 cm)
<BR>
ISSN 0004-7139
<P>
<DL>
<DT>
Subscription rates (1995):
<P>
<DD>
(a)  Yearly subscription of 24 issues and the half-year index on
microfiche:
<BR>
6920 Austrian Schillings + airmail charges from Vienna:
<BR>
3500 Austrian Schillings
<BR>
Cumulative Indexes will be sent by surface mail.
<p><DD>
(b)  Yearly subscription of 24 issues only:
<BR>
5700 Austrian Schillings + airmail charges from Vienna: 
<BR>
3500 Austrian Schillings
<p><DD>
(c)  Annual Cumulative Index in print:
1700 Austrian Schillings
<p><DD>
(d)  Price per single issue of Nos 1-24:
280 Austrian Schillings
</DL>
<P>
In addition, the INIS ATOMINDEX 1996 products are available on COM microfiche (to be
ordered from the INIS Clearinghouse):
<P> <DD>
Yearly index 1995:
<BR>
<DD>440 Austrian Schillings
<P><DD>
4 years cumulative index (1992-1995):
<BR>
<DD>1470 Austrian Schillings
<P></DL>
All COM products are supplied at the 42 ratio only and are delivered by airmail to overseas
destinations without extra charge.

<P>
<B>
INIS Reference Series
</B>
<P>
The INIS Reference Series defines the rules, standards, formats,
codes and authority lists on which the International Nuclear
Information System is based. Over the years most manuals have
been revised or merged, and further revisions will be issued in
the future. The series consists of 12 current manuals, all of
which are available in print and on microfiche and are described
below.
<P>
<B>
INIS: Guide to Bibliographic Description
<BR>
<I>INIS Reference Series No. 1</I>
</B>
<P>
This manual (formerly published under the title `Descriptive
Cataloguing Rules') contains the rules, standards and formats
for bibliographic descriptions adopted by centres preparing input
to INIS. The rules are presented in a simplified style and
several examples are provided to clarify the texts. Various
appendices are included, among them: the INIS character set; the
INIS rules for entering romanized chinese personal names; a list
of corporate abbreviations; and a list of state and province
codes for several countries. Also included in this current
revision is the information contained in INIS: Terminology and
Codes for Countries and International Organizations (IAEA-INIS-5)
and INIS: Transliteration Rules for Selected Non-Roman
Characters (IAEA-INIS-10). This manual is intended to be used in
conjunction with a companion volume entitled INIS: Descriptive
Cataloguing Samples (IAEA-INIS-2).
<P>
IAEA-INIS-1 (Rev. 8) (198 pp., 21 x 30 cm; 1992)
<BR>
ISBN 92-0-104892-0
<BR>
Price: 520 Austrian Schillings
<P>
<B>
INIS:  Samples for Bibliographic Description
<BR>
<I>INIS Reference Series No. 2</I>
</B>
<P>
This manual contains samples prepared in accordance with
IAEA-INIS-8 (Rev. 8):  Guide to Bibliographic description.  The
samples contain all the parts required for submitting records to
INIS, i.e. the bibliographic and indexing parts as well as the
abstract.
<P>
IAEA-INIS-2 (Rev. 6) (55 pp., 21 x 30 cm;  1995)
<BR>
ISBN 92-0-100795-7
<BR>
Price:  120 Austrian Schillings
<P>
<B>
INIS: Subject Categories and Scope Descriptions
<BR>
<I>INIS Reference Series No. 3</I>
</B>
<P>
This manual serves two purposes: it defines the subject scope of
INIS as well as its subject classification scheme. The INIS
subject scope covers all aspects of the peaceful uses of nuclear
science and technology. From 1992 the scope was expanded to
include the economic and environmental aspects of all energy
sources.
<P>
IAEA-INIS-3 (Rev.7) (111 pp., 21 x 30 cm; 1991)
<BR>
ISBN 92-0-178191-1
<BR>
Price: 160 Austrian Schillings
<P>
<B>
INIS: Instructions for Submitting Abstracts
<BR>
<I>INIS Reference Series No. 4</I>
</B>
<P>
This revision of IAEA-INIS-4 provides up-to-date rules on the
formal submission of abstracts to INIS, as well as a guide to the
techniques of abstracting. It is meant not only for writers of
abstracts but also for those who may be guided by the abstract in
selecting input and those whose critical assessment of what
constitutes a useful, acceptable and informative abstract may
give rise to feedback to the document source. Thus the manual
acts as a guide to progressive improvement in the quality of
accompanying abstracts.
<P>
IAEA-INIS-4 (Rev. 2) (28 pp., 21 x 30 cm; 1988)
<BR>
ISBN 92-0-178488-0
<BR>
Price: 30 Austrian Schillings
<P>
<B>
INIS:  Authority List for Corporate Entries and Report Number
Prefixes
<BR>
<I>INIS Reference Series No. 6</I>
</B>
<P>
This manual contains the standardized names of 32 403
organizations reported to INIS as corporate authors, issuing
bodies or funding organizations together with a unique
seven-digit code and country code.  Part I lists the corporate
entries in alphabetical order under the countries in which they
are located, except for international organizations that are INIS
participants;  these appear in this part as separate entries by
their names.  Part II contains an alphabetical list of all
corporate entries, followed by all report number prefixes linked
to them.  Part III lists all the report number prefixes used in
connection with the corporate entry names.
<P>
IAEA-INIS-6 (Rev. 26) (607 pp., 21 x 30 cm;  1995)
<BR>
ISBN 92-0-101595-X
<BR>
Price:  880 Austrian Schillings
<P>
<B>
INIS: Specifications for Machine Readable
Data Exchange
<BR>
<I>INIS Reference Series No. 7</I>
</B>
<P>
This manual combines the former IAEA-INIS-7 (Rev. 2) INIS:
Character Set Representation and Coding Rules with the obsolete
IAEA-INIS-8 (Rev. 1) INIS: Paper Tape Specifications and Record
Format and the obsolete IAEA-INIS-9 (Rev. 3) INIS: Magnetic Tape
Specifications and Record Format. It contains the revised INIS
character set and representations of it, together with encoding
rules for the exchange format and, specifically for input, the
worksheet format on magnetic tape and diskette. It is divided
into three parts: Part I: Character set and encoding rules; Part
II: Worksheet format on magnetic tape and diskette; Part III:
Magnetic tape exchange format and specifications (corresponding
to ISO Standard 2709). The INIS 8-bit code is an extension of the
ISO Standard 646 physical character set for information
interchange. The document also contains instructions on how to
encode symbols occurring in scientific and technical texts.
<P>
IAEA-INIS-7 (Rev. 3) (47 pp., 21 x 30 cm; 1988)
<BR>
ISBN 92-0-178588-0
<BR>
Price: 60 Austrian Schillings
<P>
<B>
INIS:  Authority List for Journal Titles
<BR>
<I>INIS Reference Series No. 11</I>
</B>
<P>
The twenty-second revision of this manual contains the names of
11 696 journal titles covered by INIS.  In Part I of the
publication, journal titles are grouped by country or
international organization responsible for the processing of that
journal for INIS.  Within that group they are ordered
alphabetically by full journal title.  In Part II the journals
are arranged in alphabetical order by full journal title,
followed by ISSN and/or CODEN if available, and country in
parentheses.  Journals marked with an asterisk are regularly
scanned for INIS.  
<P>
IAEA-INIS-11 (Rev. 22) (337 pp., 21 x 30 cm;  1995)
<BR>
ISBN 92-0-102595-5
<BR>
Price:  520 Austrian Schillings
<P>
<B>
INIS: Manual for Indexing
<BR>
<I>INIS Reference Series No. 12</I>
</B>
<P>
This manual gives the rules to be followed when preparing the
subject description of the literature reported to INIS. It must
be used in conjunction with the INIS Thesaurus (IAEA-INIS-13) and
gives detailed instructions on how to select index terms
(descriptors), and the headings for the subject index used in
INIS Atomindex.
<P>
IAEA-INIS-12 (Rev. 2) (108 pp., 21 x 30 cm; 1974)
<BR>
ISBN 92-0-178074-5
<BR>
Price: 30 Austrian Schillings
<P>
<B>
INIS: Thesaurus
<BR>
<I>INIS Reference Series No. 13</I>
</B>
<P>
The Thesaurus gives the controlled vocabulary to be used by INIS
members to index the literature they report to INIS.  This
authority ensures consistent subject indexing.  Revision 34
contains 19 701 accepted terms (descriptors) and 6184 forbidden
terms (non-descriptors).  The terms are listed alphabetically,
and with each alphabetic entry a 'word block' containing all the
terms associated with that particular entry is displayed.  A
revision of the Thesaurus is issued once a year;  cumulative
updates are normally issued monthly.
<P>
IAEA-INIS-13 (Rev. 34) (976 pp., 21 x 30 cm;  1995)
<BR>
ISBN 92-0-105294-4
<BR>
Price:  1400 Austrian Schillings
<P>
<B>
Thesaurus del Sistema Internacional de           
Documentaci&oacute;n Nuclear INIS
(Versi&oacute;n Espa&ntilde;ola)
<BR>
<I>INIS Reference Series No. 13/S</I>
</B>
<P>
The Thesaurus gives the Spanish translation of the controlled
vocabulary to be used by INIS members to index the literature
they report to INIS. This authority ensures consistent
subject indexing. Revision 32 of the Spanish version contains 19
422 accepted terms (descriptors) and 6065 forbidden terms
(non-descriptors). The terms are listed alphabetically in
Spanish, followed by the English equivalent, and with each
alphabetic entry a `word block' containing all the terms
associated with that particular entry is displayed.
<P>
IAEA-INIS-13/S (Rev. 32) (1032 pp., 21 x 30 cm; 1994)
<BR>
ISBN 92-0-300194-8
<BR>
Price: 1400 Austrian Schillings
<P>
<B>
INIS: Manual for Online Retrieval
<BR>
<I>INIS Reference Series No. 17</I>
</B>
<P>
This manual describes the INIS/STAIRS database installed on the
IAEA mainframe computer and the IAEA/STAIRS retrieval language.
It is addressed to users of the INIS Online Services of the IAEA.
The retrieval system used at the IAEA for its bibliographic data
bases is IBM/STAIRS (Storage And Information Retrieval System).
STAIRS is a multipurpose software package which enables the user
to interactively search and retrieve bibliographic data: both
online and batch retrieval are possible from the INIS database.
<P>
IAEA-INIS-17 (Rev. 2) (147 pp., 21 x 30 cm; 1984)
<BR>
ISBN 92-0-178184-9
<BR>
Price: 170 Austrian Schillings
<P>
<B>
INIS:  Multilingual Dictionary
Part I:  English - French - German - Russian - Spanish
<BR>
<I>INIS Reference Series No. 20</I>
<P>
INIS:  Dictionnaire Multilingue
PARTIE II: Fran&ccedil;ais - Anglais - Allemand - Russe -
Espagnol 
<P>
INIS:  Mehrsprachiges W&ouml;rterbuch
TEIL III:  Deutsch - Englisch - Franz&ouml;sisch - Russisch -
Spanisch
</B>
<P>
<I>(Russ. title to be inserted)</I>
<P>
<B>
INIS:  Diccionario Multilingue
PARTE V:  Espa&ntilde;ol - Ingles - Aleman - Frances - Ruso
</B>
<P>
This publication, issued in five parts, contains the terminology
of the INIS Thesaurus (IAEA-INIS-13) translated from English into
French, German, Russian and Spanish.  Each of the five parts is
sorted alphabetically by the first-named language.  The
multilingual dictionary is intended as a tool to assist INIS
users whose mother tongue is not English. It may also be useful
to others in the nuclear field such as translators, interpreters
and authors who are confronted with specialized terminology in
any of the five languages named.  
<P>
IAEA-INIS-20 (Rev. 1) (E, F, G, R or S)
<P>
Part I (585 pp., 21 x 30 cm; 1995)
<BR>
E ISBN 92-0-101995-5
<P>
Part II (582 pp., 21 x 30 cm; 1995)
<BR>
F ISBN 92-0-202695-5
<P>
Part III (553 pp., 21 x 30 cm;  1995)
<BR>
G ISBN 92-0-702795-X
<P>
Part IV (561 pp., 21 x 30 cm;  1995)
<BR>
R ISBN 92-0-402895-0
<P>
Part V (578 pp., 21 x 30 cm; 1995)
<BR>
S ISBN 92-0-302995-8
<P>
Price per Part:  880 Austrian Schillings
<P>
<B>
INIS: Guidelines for Standardized Entry of
Corporate Bodies
<BR>
<I>INIS Reference Series No. 21</I>
</B>
<P>
In the literature reported to INIS, corporate bodies are often
cited in several different ways. This makes their identification
and retrieval difficult or incomplete.
<P>
This manual provides guidelines for entering the names of
corporate bodies in a standardized form. It includes a definition
of the corporate body and how to identify, select and enter its
name. IAEA-INIS-21 is a companion manual to IAEA-INIS-6, INIS:
Authority List for Corporate Entries and Report Number Prefixes.
<P>
IAEA-INIS-21 (58 pp., 21 x 30 cm; 1989)
<BR>
ISBN 92-0-178189-X
<BR>
Price: 80 Austrian Schillings
<P>
<B>
INIS: Database Manual
<BR>
<I>INIS Reference Series No. 22</I>
</B>
<P>
This manual provides information for users of INIS output data on
magnetic media. It gives a description of each data element
including information on contents, structure and usage, and a
historical overview of additions, deletions and changes of data
elements and their contents that have taken place over the years.
<P>
IAEA-INIS-22 (39 pp., 21 x 30 cm; 1990)
<BR>
ISBN 92-0-178190-3
<BR>
Price: 60 Austrian Schillings
<P>
<B>
INIS:  Fibre User's Manual
</B>
<P>
This manual provides information and guidance on how to use the
FIBRE (Friendly Inputting of Bibliographic Records) software at
INIS input centres to prepare and submit records to be included
in the INIS database.  The manual also provides information on
how to install the software.
<P>
IAEA-INIS-23 (103 pp.,  21 x 30 cm;  1995)
<BR>
ISBN 92-0-100295-5
<BR>
Price:  200 Austrian Schillings
<P>
<B>
INIS Input Training Kit
</B>
<P>
The INIS Input Training Kit is a self-contained, step-by-step
guide to input preparation for INIS, with working examples. It is
equally useful for instructors and for self-instruction. It
consists of five parts, as follows: Part I: Kit utilization
module (KUM), Subject analysis module (SAM); Part II: SAM:
Documents for indexing and abstracting; Part III: Worksheet pads;
Part IV: Descriptive cataloguing module (DCM); Part V: Two audio
cassettes treating subject analysis and descriptive cataloguing.
<P>
STI/PUB/653 (844 pp., 21 x 30 cm; 1983)
<BR>
ISBN 92-0-179083-X
<BR>
Price: 1010 Austrian Schillings
