STI/PUB/877 (501 pp., 65 figures; 1991)<BR>
ISBN 92-0-150091-2<BR>
Price: 1300 Austrian Schillings
<P>
<B>Environmental Assessment Methodologies for Sea Dumping of
Radioactive Wastes<BR>
<I>Safety Series No. 65</I></B>
<P> 
The purpose of this book is to provide guidance and information
on the nature and content of the environmental assessment
required for permit applications for sea dumping of radioactive
wastes. The environmental assessment, to be submitted by the
national licensing authority to the International Maritime
Organization, must first explain the necessity for sea dumping,
secondly describe the characteristics of the waste and the
dumping, and thirdly assess the impact of the proposed dumping
operation. This document primarily deals with the scientific and
technical considerations included in environmental assessment
documents. 
<P>
<I>Contents:</I> Introduction; Selection of methods for the
management of radioactive wastes; Assessment of sea dumping;
Content of an environmental assessment document; Conclusions. 
