<HEAD>
<TITLE>
1996 PUBLICATIONS
</TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR=#ffffff>
<CENTER>
<H2>
International Nuclear Information System (INIS)
</H2>
<P>
</CENTER>
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<B>INIS:  THESAURUS<BR>
<I>INIS Reference Series No. 13</I>
</B>
<P>
The Thesaurus gives the controlled vocabulary to be used by
INIS members to index the literature they report to INIS. 
This authority ensures consistent subject indexing.  Revision
35 contains 19743 accepted terms (descriptors) and 6228
forbidden terms (non-descriptors).  The terms are listed
alphabetically, and with each entry a 'word block' containing
all the terms associated with that particular entry is
displayed.  A revision of the Thesaurus is issued once a year; 
cumulative updates are normally issued monthly.
<P>
IAEA-INIS-13 (Rev. 35) (978 pp., 21 x 30 cm;  1996)
<BR>
ISBN 92-0-104595-6
<BR>
Price:  1400 Austrian Schillings
<P>
<B>INIS:  MANUAL FOR SUBJECT ANALYSIS <BR>
<I>INIS Reference Series No. 12</I> 
</B>
<P>
This manual covers the subject analysis part of input
preparation, including document selection, subject
classification, abstracting and subject indexing.  It presents
the rules, guidelines and procedures to be adopted by centres
submitting input to the INIS Database.  The manual should be
used in conjunction with the INIS Thesaurus (IAEA-INIS-13),
the Subject Categories and Scope Descriptions (IAEA-INIS-3)
and the Instructions for Submitting Abstracts (IAEA-INIS-4). 
It also constitutes part of the ETDE (Energy Technology Data
Exchange) Procedures Manual.
<P>
IAEA-INIS-12 (Rev. 3) (79 pp., 21 x 30 cm; 1996)
<BR>
ISBN 92-0-100696-9
<BR>
Price:  200 Austrian Schillings
<P>
<B>INIS:  AUTHORITY LIST FOR JOURNAL TITLES
<BR>
<I>INIS Reference Series No. 11</I>
</B>
<P>
The twenty-third revision of this manual contains the names of
11 745 journal titles covered by INIS.  In Part I of the publication,
journal titles are grouped by country or international organization
responsible for their processing for INIS.  Within the groups they
are ordered alphabetically by full journal title.  In Part II the
journals are arranged in alphabetical order by full journal title,
followed by ISSN and/or CODEN if available, and country in
parentheses.  Journals marked with an asterisk are regularly scanned
for INIS.  
<P>
IAEA-INIS-11 (Rev. 23) (326 pp., 21 x 30 cm;  1996)
<BR>
ISBN 92-0-102796-6
<BR>
Price:  520 Austrian Schillings
<P>
<B>INIS:  AUTHORITY LIST FOR CORPORATE ENTRIES AND REPORT NUMBER PREFIXES 
<BR>
<I>INIS Reference Series No. 6</I></B>
<P>
This manual contains the standardized names of 32 098 organizations reported to INIS as corporate authors, issuing bodies or funding organizations together with a unique seven-digit code and country code.  Part I lists the corporate entries in alphabetical order under the countries in which they are located, except for international organizations that are INIS participants; these appear in this part as separate entries, in alphabetical order, by their names.  Part II contains an alphabetical list of all corporate entries, followed by all report number prefixes linked to them. Part III lists all the report number prefixes used in connection with the corporate entry names. 
<P>
IAEA-INIS-6 (Rev. 27) (626 pp.; 1996)
<BR>
ISBN 92-0-102996-9
<BR>
Price:  920 Austrian Schillings
<P>
<B>INIS:  SAMPLES FOR BIBLIOGRAPHIC DESCRIPTION
<BR>
<I>INIS Reference Series No. 2</I></B>
<P>
This manual contains samples prepared in accordance with the latest INIS cataloguing rules as set out in IAEA-INIS-1 (Rev. 8):  Guide to Bibliographic Description and its updates.  The samples contain all the parts required for submitting records to INIS, i.e. the bibliographic and indexing parts as well as the abstract, but the comments focus on aspects of bibliographic description.
<P>
IAEA-INIS-2 (Rev. 7) (55 p., 21 x 30 cm;  1996)
<BR>
ISBN 92-0-103896-8
<BR>
Price:  120 Austrian Schillings
<P>
<HR>
<P>
<CENTER>
<A HREF="index96.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/worldatom/publications/grafix/button_n.gif" align=right ALT=Next></A>

<A HREF="96wm.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/worldatom/publications/grafix/button_p.gif" align=left ALT=Previous></A>

<A HREF="index96.html"><IMG BORDER=0 SRC="/worldatom/publications/grafix/button_m.gif" align=center ALT=Main></A>
<P>
</CENTER>
