<HR SIZE=1 NOSHADE>
<CENTER><H3>Communication received from the Resident
Representative of Italy on behalf of the European Community</H3>
<P>
<B><I>
A communication dated 21 December 1995 from the Permanent Mission
of Finland</I></B>
</CENTER>
<P>
<OL>
<LI>On 2 January 1996, the Director General received a note
verbale of 21 December 1995 from the Permanent Mission of Finland
containing information about Finland's policy regarding transfers
of nuclear material, equipment and technology between the Member
States of the European Community as set out in document
<A HREF="inf322.html">INFCIRC/322</A>.
<P>
<LI>As requested by the Permanent Mission of Finland, the text of
the note verbale is being circulated for the information of
Member States of the Agency.
</OL>
<P>
<HR NOSHADE SIZE=1>
<P>
<CENTER>
<H3>
Text of a Note Verbale Dated 21 December 1995 to the Director
General from the Permanent Mission of Finland</H3>
</CENTER>
<P>
The Permanent Mission of Finland presents its compliments to the
Director General of the International Atomic Energy Agency and
has the honour to inform him, that the Government of Finland as
Member State of the European Union as of 1 January 1995 has upon
accession to the European Union adopted the common policy
declaration adopted on 20 November 1984 by the ministers for
foreign affairs of the then ten members of the European
Community, which was transmitted to the Director General by the
Resident Representative of Italy, on behalf of the Community, on
22 March 1985 and which is reproduced in document <A
HREF="inf322.html">INFCIRC/322</A>.
The declaration deals with transfers of nuclear material,
equipment and technology between the Member States of the
European Community.
<P>
The Government of Finland would be grateful if the Director
General were to bring this Note to the attention of the Member
States of the IAEA.
<P>
The Permanent Mission of Finland avails itself of this
opportunity to renew to the Director General of the International
Atomic Energy Agency the assurances of its highest consideration.
<P>
<HR NOSHADE SIZE=1>
