<HR SIZE=1 NOSHADE>
<CENTER><H3><SMALL>Communication Received from the Resident
Representative of Italy on Behalf of
the European Community</SMALL>
<P>
A Communication Dated 17 June 1996 from the Permanent Mission of
Austria</H3></CENTER>
<P>
<OL>
<LI>On 19 June 1996, the Director General received a note verbale
of 17 June 1996 from the Permanent Mission
of Austria about the adoption, by the Government of Austria, of
the common policy declaration adopted on 20
November 1984 by the ministers for foreign affairs of the then
ten members of the European Community. This was
transmitted to the Director General by the Resident
Representative of Italy on behalf of the Community on
22 March 1985 and is reproduced in <A
HREF="inf322.html">INFCIRC/322</A>.
<P>
<LI>As requested by the Government of Austria, the text of its
note verbale of 17 June 1996 is being circulated
for the information of Member States of the Agency.
</OL>
<P>
<HR NOSHADE SIZE=1>
<P ALIGN=RIGHT>
<I>INFCIRC/322/Add.4
<BR>
Attachment</I>
</P>
<CENTER>
<B>TEXT OF A NOTE VERBALE DATED 17 JUNE 1996
TO THE DIRECTOR GENERAL FROM
THE PERMANENT MISSION OF AUSTRIA</B>
</CENTER>
<P>
The Permanent Mission of Austria presents its compliments to the
Director General of the International Atomic
Energy Agency and has the honour to inform him, that the
Government of Austria as Member State of the European
Union as of 1 January 1995 has upon accession to the European
Union adopted the common policy declaration
adopted on 20 November 1984 by the ministers for foreign affairs
of the then ten members of the European
Community, which was transmitted to the Director General by the
Resident Representative of Italy on behalf of the
Community on 22 March 1985 and which is reproduced in document <A
HREF="inf322.html">INFCIRC/322</A>. The declaration deals with
transfers of nuclear material, equipment and
technology between the Member States of the European Union.
<P>
The Government of Austria would be grateful if the Director
General were to bring this Note to the attention of the
Member States of the IAEA.
<P>
The Permanent Mission of Austria avails itself of this
opportunity to renew to the Director General of the
International Atomic Energy Agency the assurances of its highest
consideration.
<P>
